$interpreted:
Leah: I've collected all the materials Miss Lucien required.
Why hasn't she come to pick them up yet?
Betty: Leah~ Someone sent this to you.
Leah: Don't tell me... Did Lio once again...
Leah: Why did he return the present I mailed him YET AGAIN!
Leah: I can't take this anymore!! I'm going to find him and give him a good spanking!!
Nigel: What is it this time? His bawling is so loud that you can hear him outside the door.

Hyacinthus: Just now... Lio received a package...
It seems like Leah mailed back Lio's Moonstone gift once again.

Lio: *Sobs*... Sis... she must still be really angry...
What should I do... to get sis to forgive me...
Nigel: Then why don't you go ask her yourself?
Nigel: If all you did was sulk and mumble about random nonsense here, you're not getting a good answer anyway.
Lio: OK, I'll go ask sister about why she just wouldn't forgive me!
Lio: I won't come back unless she forgives me!
Nigel: Sighs~
Lio: Ow ow ow... Eh?
Leah: Damnit! Watch where you are going! You...
Leah: Lio!? I was just on my way to visit you!
Lio: Hmm? Those items on the ground...
Lio: Sis!? Why do you have so many Pomelodoras and Moonstones?
Lio: Wait, could it be that... Sis, did you also...
Leah: ...... Pffffft, Puhahahaha!
Lio: Haha, I thought~
Lio: I really thought sis disliked me and don't want to see me again...
Leah: ... You dumb little boy. No way in the world will I ever dislike you.
Leah: Hehe, my Pomelodoras are indeed sweeter~
Lio: What are you talking about? Mine are sweeter; has more moisture too!
Leah: Really? Lemme have a taste!
Lio: Ah, Sis, look~
Lio: The moon is so big and round today!
Leah: You're right! It appears to be much closer to us too...
Lio: This Moonstone seems to shine even brighter under the moonlight!
Leah: Who's there!?
Puggi: Guhehehehe~ Are you guys wondering why I popped out all of a sudden?
Puggi: It's the Mid-Autumn Festival! Such a grand event calls for the appearance of Puggi whether it makes sense or not!
Puggi: Pomelodoras! Juice! They're all MINE!!!
Leah: Ah! Idiot! That's not juice!
Puggi: Cough! Eww... tastes so gross... Ughhhhhh...
Puggi: Ugh... no carrots... All carrots must die!!
Lio: Sis... did that weird bird really just fly to the moon?
Leah: Who cares.
Leah: Sighs~ Miss Lucien is going to be SO mad...
Lio: I'll go with sis and apologize to her together. Is that ok?
Leah: ... Sure. Then I'll carry these Pomelodoras back to the Slums with you, together!
Lio: Yes! Nigel and Cin will be so happy to see you!
